1.title: Cast Evaluation

episode of.title: It's Not My Show! (The Craig Show) (TV Series 2013– )

1.plot: Season 4 Premiere! The cast and crew are under evaluation by the Network Executive for their wild and weird behavior. How will the cast do? Will they pass?

2.title: It's Not My Public Access Show

episode of.title: It's Not My Show! (The Craig Show) (TV Series 2013– )

2.plot: Under rule of the Network Executive, Craig and crew have to follow a script of a traditional public access program. Segments include current events, a psychological showcase as well as an open public forum.

3.title: ARMmageddon

episode of.title: It's Not My Show! (The Craig Show) (TV Series 2013– )

3.plot: The cast and crew combat in an arm wrestling tournament, but what happens when the Network Executive is overlooking? Who will win the tournament and be crowned the first ever ARMmageddon Champion?

4.title: The Floor Is Lava

episode of.title: It's Not My Show! (The Craig Show) (TV Series 2013– )

4.plot: The Entourage have taken over the show and put the cast and crew through an old fashioned game of "The Floor is Lava." There's only one rule, don't touch the floor.

5.title: Midas Media Presents: Another Jack Havick Episode

episode of.title: It's Not My Show! (The Craig Show) (TV Series 2013– )

5.plot: Another Jack Havick Episode! In this episode Midas Media and Jack Havick invite the cast of The Craig Show to his pool party along with the Network Executive to make sure everything runs smooth. Also, music appearance by Cold Collective!

6.title: The Insult Battle

episode of.title: It's Not My Show! (The Craig Show) (TV Series 2013– )

6.plot: The Season 4 Finale. Craig, Gee and Scott take on Jack Havick and his Entourage in an insult battle. The winner will have sole control of the show.

1.title: Movies

episode of.title: It's Not My Show! (The Craig Show) (TV Series 2013– )

1.plot: This was our first episode, We were still working out a lot of the kinks in this thing but it turned out very good. Well, it turned out okay. Even I have to admit, the scripts were awkward and not as funny as we thought they would be (especially mine). There were still some great moments like Brandon mispronouncing "uber" and Phil's rap performance. Plus, we are first introduced to the unique personality of The Real Rock. -Craig

2.title: Rap Battle

episode of.title: It's Not My Show! (The Craig Show) (TV Series 2013– )

2.plot: The rap battle episode! We put out a challenge to the entire town to get rappers to challenge us to rap battles and...no one show up (cough,,,cowards...cough). Anyways, we had fun and things kinda got personal towards the end of it. We also see the start of a beautiful relationship between The Real Rock and Mike Gee. One more thing, the first rap battle will be forever lost in space and time because the sound was not turned on (sorry not sorry...why did I write that) -Craig

3.title: Patriotic Pajama Party

episode of.title: It's Not My Show! (The Craig Show) (TV Series 2013– )

3.plot: Everyone expresses Patriotism is their own way. This episode is the way we expressed our patriotism with dancing, celebration, story-telling, truth or dare and pajamas. There was a lot happening in this episode and it was so fun. Our buddy Max made his debut on the show and he was great. Also, Brandon provided us with one of the saddest moments ever on the show with the ending he came up with to our story (it really caused the audience to get upset). -Craig

4.title: Nice-Off Talent Show

episode of.title: It's Not My Show! (The Craig Show) (TV Series 2013– )

4.plot: We force everyone to be nice and of course that got weird. Max rejoins us and we see the debut of Kyle and Scott (some of the nicest guys you will ever meet). Brandon and I get very, very personal and I get legitimately mad at everyone in this episode, so much so that I didn't talk to anyone for a couple of days after it ended. -Craig

5.title: Is This Fashion?

episode of.title: It's Not My Show! (The Craig Show) (TV Series 2013– )

5.plot: The Real Rock left, Gee left and I have complete control of the show so we decide to take on the wonderful world of fashion! And guess what we learned? NONE OF US HAVE FASHION! My good friend Victor makes his debut as well as we get to see the on camera debut of Paul the Cameraman (he's kind of a jerk). Also, two words: Coach. Sweaty. -Craig

6.title: The Real Rock Rules

episode of.title: It's Not My Show! (The Craig Show) (TV Series 2013– )

6.plot: The Real Rock takes over the show. I hated it. There's a lot of violence. -Craig

7.title: Team Craig vs. Team Rock Season Finale Trivia Showdown Extravaganza

episode of.title: It's Not My Show! (The Craig Show) (TV Series 2013– )

7.plot: THE SEASON FINALE! My feud with The Real Rock reaches its boiling point with a trivia team showdown. Old friends rejoin us and new friends (enemies?) are introduced. Joe and Brandon wear suits. Good times were had and great memories were made. (The name of this episode is way too long.) -Craig

8.title: Telekinetic Twin Trip of Terror (Halloween Special)

episode of.title: It's Not My Show! (The Craig Show) (TV Series 2013– )

8.plot: Our Halloween Special! The cast and crew put Gee and Joe through the Telekinetic Twin Trip of Terror (because they're twins after all).

9.title: American Gladiator Holiday Carol (Christmas Special)

episode of.title: It's Not My Show! (The Craig Show) (TV Series 2013– )

9.plot: Our Holiday Special! Truly a magical time! We answer the prolific question: What happens when Charles Dickens meets American Gladiators? Well, here is the answer. This one got insane! Oh, and Mike looks like an elf in this episode too. -Craig

10.title: Spring Walk (Special)

episode of.title: It's Not My Show! (The Craig Show) (TV Series 2013– )

10.plot: Craig walks the whole length of Stoneham, from one end of Main Street to the other. Along the way, the Real Rock has set up obstacles to prevent Craig from completing his journey. Many familiar faces as well as new ones make some funny appearances during the 3 mile trek.

1.title: Where's Craig?

episode of.title: It's Not My Show! (The Craig Show) (TV Series 2013– )

1.plot: The first episode of Season 2. After Craig mysteriously went missing in the season one finale, Joe and Mike attempt to find his whereabouts. Will they find Craig or will the show still be without its host?

2.title: Wide World of Sports

episode of.title: It's Not My Show! (The Craig Show) (TV Series 2013– )

2.plot: Craig finally has control of the show back after he went missing. The panel is put to the challenge of competing against each other in a series of sporting events. They are commentated by guest star and fan of the show, Robbie Johnson along side none other than football star himself, Tim Tebow.

3.title: Make the Nice Kids Angry

episode of.title: It's Not My Show! (The Craig Show) (TV Series 2013– )

3.plot: Episode 3 of Season 2 is a callback to Season 1's 4th episode: The Nice-Off Talent Show. The Nice Kids are back and this time the panel is challenged with the task to get them mad! Will they succeed? Batman might.

4.title: Arts and Music Festival

episode of.title: It's Not My Show! (The Craig Show) (TV Series 2013– )

4.plot: The panel have to sketch live models but the catch is, none of them can draw!! Special guest artist and friend of the show, Dan Brenton, makes an appearance. Also, live music from Off & On.

5.title: Breaking Memories

episode of.title: It's Not My Show! (The Craig Show) (TV Series 2013– )

5.plot: ...or as we like to call it "Chuckie." The cast had their personal items stolen and held hostage by The Executioner. They have to complete 60 second challenges in order to save their precious items, if they cannot complete their challenges, their items will be broken into a million pieces.

6.title: What Would You Do on the Craig Show?

episode of.title: It's Not My Show! (The Craig Show) (TV Series 2013– )

6.plot: Each panel member gets an opportunity to live out their dreams by doing whatever they want to do. This episode becomes a little uneasy when yet another "sabotage" occurs. And also, A-Rod makes an appearance!

7.title: The Spirit Journey

episode of.title: It's Not My Show! (The Craig Show) (TV Series 2013– )

7.plot: Craig embarks on a spiritual journey to figure out who's sabotaging the show. He enters the "Netherrealm" and encounters some weird, yet familiar people.

8.title: Craig's Court

episode of.title: It's Not My Show! (The Craig Show) (TV Series 2013– )

8.plot: Craig is the judge of his own court and each panel member gets put on the stand as Craig tries to figure out who's been behind the season long sabotages.

9.title: The Exorcism of the Freak

episode of.title: It's Not My Show! (The Craig Show) (TV Series 2013– )

9.plot: The cast and crew of The Craig Show attempt to exorcise the demon that inhabits their friend and cast member, Scott. Can it be done? This episode gets a little bit creepy.

10.title: The Holiday Swap

episode of.title: It's Not My Show! (The Craig Show) (TV Series 2013– )

10.plot: The cast and crew engage in a Holiday Swap to celebrate the holidays. Presents will be traded and wrapping paper will be flying.

11.title: The Craig Show Awards

episode of.title: It's Not My Show! (The Craig Show) (TV Series 2013– )

11.plot: Time to break out the elegant dresses and tuxedos! It's award time! The first ever Craig Show Awards are finally here! Watch as the cast and crew anxiously await the results of the award categories. Who will win? Will Kanye show up?

1.title: The Airing of Grievances

episode of.title: It's Not My Show! (The Craig Show) (TV Series 2013– )

1.plot: The first episode of Season 3. The show has been taken over by Joe, Jack and Scott and they have tied up Craig.The trio bring back cast and crew members to come on and talk about the things they don't like about Craig. Also, new segments including Scott's Character Corner and You Don't Know Jack!

2.title: Does Craig Know the Show?

episode of.title: It's Not My Show! (The Craig Show) (TV Series 2013– )

2.plot: Joe, Scott and Jack still have control of the show and Craig is still tied up. Craig is asked questions about the show's past episodes and cast members and if he gets them wrong, a consequence ensues. If he gets the question right, then a consequence happens to Gee. Also, new segments of Scott's Character Corner and You Don't Know Jack. Does Craig know the show as well as you think?

3.title: Show Improvements

episode of.title: It's Not My Show! (The Craig Show) (TV Series 2013– )

3.plot: Joe and Scott still have full control over Craig's show. In this episode, Joe and Scott recall bits from episodes from the past seasons and attempt to make them better. It involves a piñata.

4.title: Villain Tryouts

episode of.title: It's Not My Show! (The Craig Show) (TV Series 2013– )

4.plot: Episode 4 of Season 3. Craig is still held captive by Producer Joe, Jack Havick and Scott. The trio hold "Villain Tryouts" and open up the floor to anyone who wants to be a villain and tryout to be in their group. The tryouts come to a quick end when a special guest appears and ruins their segment.

5.title: The Initiation

episode of.title: It's Not My Show! (The Craig Show) (TV Series 2013– )

5.plot: Craig has joined forces with the trio: Producer Joe, Scott and Jack Havick, and put him through their initiation. There are 3 steps to initiation to test his worthiness, mental, physical and emotional. Will Craig pass and become a member of the trio or will The Real Rock come back and save him?

6.title: The Jack Havick Special

episode of.title: It's Not My Show! (The Craig Show) (TV Series 2013– )

6.plot: The episode everyone everywhere have been waiting for! The episode fully dedicated to the "Pulverizing Pizazz Policy Maker" himself, Jack Havick. Watch as Mr. Havick does what he wants, when he wants during this half hour excursion. He punches things, wrestles, and talks about Star Wars.

7.title: The Jack Havick Wrestling Academy Presents Switch'em Up Roulette

episode of.title: It's Not My Show! (The Craig Show) (TV Series 2013– )

7.plot: The Jack Havick Wrestling Academy is in session. Watch as Jack Havick teaches the cast how to do some nifty wrestling moves while the remainder of the cast and crew participate in Switch'em Up Roulette. Special appearances by our good friends Robbie and Kyle from On A Couch Talking Sports.

8.title: The Wheel of Weirdness

episode of.title: It's Not My Show! (The Craig Show) (TV Series 2013– )

8.plot: Season 3 comes to a close with the Wheel of Weirdness. The cast and crew have to spin the wheel and whatever task it lands on they must complete, if they don't then they are truly the villains of the show. Tensions rise and things get heated.

9.title: Street Frighter: Cauldron Combat (Halloween Special)

episode of.title: It's Not My Show! (The Craig Show) (TV Series 2013– )

9.plot: It's that time of year again and time for another Halloween episode! The cast and crew have to participate in a Halloween version of a fighting video game. Each member from a team will pick a pumpkin out of a cauldron in order to command their player. This one was a lot of fun.

10.title: Holiday Happenings (Season 3 Holiday Special)

episode of.title: It's Not My Show! (The Craig Show) (TV Series 2013– )

10.plot: What's gonna happen on this year's holiday special? Good question, we don't know either.

11.title: Winter Blues (Special)

episode of.title: It's Not My Show! (The Craig Show) (TV Series 2013– )

11.plot: Craig has the winter blues. How are the guys gonna cheer him up? It might not be possible.

12.title: Lasell College Radio Special

episode of.title: It's Not My Show! (The Craig Show) (TV Series 2013– )

12.plot: The cast and crew of The Craig Show take over the radio with their appearance on Lasell College Radio's Absolute Nonsense.
